I"œ<p>Cablegram [315] [1] LONDON, 10 May 1940, 8.18 p.m.</p>

<p>MOST IMMEDIATE FOR THE PRIME MINISTER HIMSELF ONLY</p>

<p>Political. Labour Party have refused to join the Government under Chamberlain but agreed to co-operate in the formation of a National Government under another Prime Minister. Chamberlain seeing the King tonight and though not definite I anticipate that Churchill will be sent for and new Government formed immediately.</p>

<p>Chamberlain has agreed to continue as member of the Cabinet.</p>

<p>BRUCE</p>

